<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16135">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Whitewater.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16136">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16136 mb-requirement-id-16137">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in whitewater activities, including branches and
        trees in water along a shore and stretching across the stream, rocks,
        hydraulics over ledges or lowhead dams, strong wind, low water or air
        temperature, and thunder and lightning storms. Explain what you should
        do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EwUVNgeO0E8" target="_blank"
          >River Features (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/VuO9ZSCtZN4" target="_blank"
          >Low-Head Dams: Get Out and Scout (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.kayakscout.com/kayaking-in-a-thunderstorm/"
          target="_blank"
          >What To Do When Kayaking in a Thunderstorm (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16136 mb-requirement-id-16138">
        (b) Review with your counselor the prevention, symptoms, and first aid
        treatment for the following injuries or illnesses that could occur while
        participating in whitewater activities including cold-water shock;
        hypothermia; head, neck, and back injuries; heat-related illnesses;
        sunburn; dehydration; blisters; bruises; cuts; sprains and strains;
        shoulder dislocation; and submersion injuries. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLxKdp8_KfCQnMeVV5WjCGLQtOk0IdR_4S"
          target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Immersion and Drowning (playlist)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16136 mb-requirement-id-16139">
        (c) Discuss with your counselor the Scouting America Safety Afloat
        policy and the American Whitewater safety guidelines, including the use
        of helmet and life jackets. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.americanwhitewater.org/explore/safety/safety-code/"
          target="_blank"
          >American Whitewater Safety Guidelines (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16140">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16140 mb-requirement-id-16141">
        (a) Demonstrate understanding of the following river features by drawing
        lines to show the flow of water: upstream V, downstream V, riffle, eddy
        with an eddy line, ledge, river bend, shallows, current at different
        depths, drop, horizon line, and hydraulic. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/luOWq1Gdv8c" target="_blank"
          >River Hydrology 101—Part 1: How To 'Read' Whitewater Rapids
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nKBrFv164xQ" target="_blank"
          >River Hydrology 101—Part 2: How To 'Read' Whitewater Rapids
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16140 mb-requirement-id-16142">
        (b) Describe how waves form including standing waves and wave trains.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://raftingescapes.com/wave-train-rafting/" target="_blank"
          >Wave Train Rafting: The Pro's Guide to Safe Navigation (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16140 mb-requirement-id-16143">
        (c) Explain how to tilt or edge the boat without leaning your body
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Tp9gcA0bBoo" target="_blank"
          >Edging Your Whitewater Kayak (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TEobm0VU7cs" target="_blank"
          >Basic Canoe Control: Edge (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16143 mb-requirement-id-16189">
        (1) When entering and exiting an eddy.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16143 mb-requirement-id-16190">
        (2) When ferrying in downstream and upstream directions.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16140 mb-requirement-id-16144">
        (d) Explain when, why, and how you should scout a river while ashore,
        while on the river, and when you should portage your boat. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qBn7YOJMK7g" target="_blank"
          >Advanced River Running—Scouting and Breaking Down Rapids (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16145">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Before doing requirements 4 through 12, earn the Canoeing merit badge if
      you will be using a canoe to earn this merit badge. If you will be using a
      kayak, earn the Kayaking merit badge. Then do ONE of the following:
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.scouting.org/merit-badges/canoeing/" target="_blank"
        >Canoeing Merit Badge (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.scouting.org/merit-badges/kayaking/" target="_blank"
        >Kayaking Merit Badge (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16145 mb-requirement-id-16146">
        (a) If you will be using a canoe to earn this merit badge, demonstrate
        strokes and maneuvers from the Canoeing merit badge to the satisfaction
        of your counselor.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16145 mb-requirement-id-16147">
        (b) If you will be using a kayak to earn this merit badge, demonstrate
        strokes and maneuvers from the Kayaking merit badge to the satisfaction
        of your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16148">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16148 mb-requirement-id-16149">
        <b>Option A—Tandem Canoest.</b> Do ALL of the following strokes and
        techniques on calm water: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/HYvucbWN4co" target="_blank"
          >Essential Strokes for Tandem Maneuvers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16149 mb-requirement-id-16150">
        (1) Demonstrate the following strokes in the bow: cross forward, bow
        draw, cross bow draw, bow pry, and sculling draw.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16149 mb-requirement-id-16151">
        (2) Demonstrate the following strokes in the stern: stern draw, stern
        pry, sculling draw, and forward with stern pry.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16149 mb-requirement-id-16152">
        (3) Demonstrate a high brace, low brace, and righting pry.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16148 mb-requirement-id-16153">
        <b>Option B—Solo Canoest.</b> Do ALL of the following strokes and
        techniques on calm water:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16153 mb-requirement-id-16154">
        (1) Demonstrate the following strokes: cross forward, bow draw, cross
        bow draw, stern draw, pry, stern pry, sculling draw, and forward with
        stern pry. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TGE6i_aIvuE" target="_blank"
          >Cross Forward Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Un04rB9qb3E" target="_blank"
          >Stationary Bow Draw (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BXc39F1F-pI" target="_blank"
          >Cross Bow Draw (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/OlhiyVmFHDg" target="_blank"
          >Running Bow Pry (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0NbWDhmREgo" target="_blank"
          >Sculling Draw (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16153 mb-requirement-id-16155">
        (2) Demonstrate a high brace, low brace, and righting pry. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-HofhF4__ps" target="_blank"
          >How To Keep Your Canoe From Flipping—Low and High Braces (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16148 mb-requirement-id-16156">
        <b>Option C—Solo Kayaker.</b> Do ALL of the following strokes and
        techniques on calm water:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16156 mb-requirement-id-16157">
        (1) Demonstrate the following strokes: bow draw, rudder, and sculling
        draw. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iGmQjKKuh10" target="_blank"
          >The Bow Draw (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DzO3ef7x45E" target="_blank"
          >Rudder Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/hXT80bHsRKA" target="_blank"
          >Draw Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0NbWDhmREgo" target="_blank"
          >Sculling Draw (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16156 mb-requirement-id-16158">
        (2) Demonstrate a high brace and low brace. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lTzVPNva_fw" target="_blank"
          >Kayak High Brace (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/B1YxQJnfFz0" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Low Brace (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16159">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16159 mb-requirement-id-16160">
        (a) Explain the International Scale of River Difficulty and apply the
        scale to the stretch of river approved by your counselor. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/g0s-MvzFRNM?si=Qy7hha_z5TIivvjk"
          target="_blank"
          >Whitewater Rafting: Rapid Classes Demystified (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16159 mb-requirement-id-16161">
        (b) Identify the specific characteristics of the river that are factors
        in your classification according to the International Scale.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16159 mb-requirement-id-16162">
        (c) Discuss how the level of flow changes a river from one class to
        another and what effects different flow rates have on the features of a
        river and its hazards.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16186">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Explain the importance of communication during every whitewater outing.
      Demonstrate knowledge and ability to use the following American Whitewater
      Universal River Signals, both visual and auditory: "Stop," "Are you OK?,"
      "Help/emergency," "Run river right," "Run river left," and "All clear—come
      ahead." <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/wnD2DQrENiQ" target="_blank"
        >Hand Signals on the River (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16163">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16163 mb-requirement-id-16164">
        (a) If completing this merit badge in a canoe, describe the various
        types of canoes used on moving water and how they differ in design,
        materials, and purpose. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://redbeardsailing.com/blogs/red-beard-report/canoe-buyers-guide"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Choose a Canoe (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16163 mb-requirement-id-16165">
        (b) If completing this merit badge in a kayak, describe the various
        types of kayaks used on moving water and explain how they differ in
        design, materials, and purpose. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qzgkUM3hoP0" target="_blank"
          >Kayaking | How To Choose a Kayak (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16187">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Review with your counselor the personal and group equipment necessary for
      a safe whitewater outing and how and why it is used. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/bu_trV7Kbx8" target="_blank"
        >Beginners Guide to Whitewater Kayaking Gear (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/lheh7gnlG3I" target="_blank"
        >Top 5 Pieces of Paddling Gear | The Essential Kayak and Canoe Gear
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16188">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Demonstrate your ability to read a Class II section of river approved by
      your counselor. Describe the most desirable paths or lines of travel as
      well as alternative routes and options. Point out how to use the existing
      water features to your advantage, and explain how to best avoid the
      hazards present.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16166">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Wearing a proper life jacket and being appropriately dressed for the
      weather and water conditions, perform the following skills in moving water
      in a properly equipped whitewater craft of your choice (tandem canoe, solo
      canoe, or solo kayak). If a tandem canoe is used, the skills must be
      demonstrated from both the bow and stern positions. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/xUUX1VI7i1I" target="_blank"
        >Kayaking Tips—Cold Water and Winter Paddling (Wear, Gear and Risks)
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jH99hBZB_l8" target="_blank"
        >How To Choose a Life Jacket for Kayaking and Canoeing (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16167">
        (a) Launch and land. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9Tdk0YKflhk" target="_blank"
          >How To Launch and Land Your Kayak (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/78qqDqUIX20&amp;t=24" target="_blank"
          >How To Launch and Land a Canoe Smoothly and Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16168">
        (b) Paddle forward in a straight line at least 10 boat lengths. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3qWfoKl7-Gs" target="_blank"
          >Whitewater Kayaking for Beginners: The Forward Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GoPN8COLz2A" target="_blank"
          >Forward Paddling for Canoes: Generating the Power (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16169">
        (c) Backpaddle in a straight line at least five boat lengths. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/oa7Q_0LM8OQ" target="_blank"
          >The Back / Reverse Stroke—Sea Kayak Technique (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XOjH3h5Cao0" target="_blank"
          >Canoeing: Paddling Backwards (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16170">
        (d) Ferry upstream from both sides of the river. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qPhBCiupQXM" target="_blank"
          >How To Ferry Your Kayak in Current (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ug7ITXafAB0" target="_blank"
          >How To Do a Back Ferry While Kayaking (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5yQSFFn24HY" target="_blank"
          >Tandem Front Ferry (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16171">
        (e) Ferry downstream from both sides of the river.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16172">
        (f) Eddy turn from both sides of an eddy. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/92AxG88R1Rc" target="_blank"
          >How To Do a Carving Eddy Turn (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1JS-7r697Rc" target="_blank"
          >Tandem Canoe Eddy Turns—Carving Using MITH (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16166 mb-requirement-id-16173">
        (g) Peel out from both sides of an eddy. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/OTVIHx48AUM" target="_blank"
          >How To Catch and Peel Out of an Eddy (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zxJRJMK-fsY" target="_blank"
          >Eddy Exits Using SHARC (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16174">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      Explain and demonstrate the following to your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16174 mb-requirement-id-16175">
        (a) Self-rescue and procedures when capsized in moving water, including
        a wet exit if necessary <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rpQ1kuhNxhQ" target="_blank"
          >How To Self Rescue in a Whitewater Kayak (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/m-0MeYKgmEs" target="_blank"
          >Canoe Self-Rescue Method: Re-Entry (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/JpF-CoXjfWU?si=huGEf8yBwEUBh-oN"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Swim Line to Self Rescue a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16174 mb-requirement-id-16176">
        (b) Proper use of a throw rope to rescue a swimmer in whitewater
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/B6dxD-ttYAw?si=L0aRNmvbjod6IPzV"
          target="_blank"
          >Throw Bag Techniques (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DbWkLJ2gKTE" target="_blank"
          >White Water Swims and Throw Bag Rescues (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UTzJsbXdHz0" target="_blank"
          >How To Perform a Throwbag Rescue (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16174 mb-requirement-id-16177">
        (c) Proper technique for receiving a throw rope as a swimmer <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/B6dxD-ttYAw" target="_blank"
          >Throw Bag Techniques (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DbWkLJ2gKTE" target="_blank"
          >White Water Swims and Throw Bag Rescues (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16174 mb-requirement-id-16178">
        (d) Portaging-where portaging would be appropriate, and when and how to
        do it <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wQKTRO-R9Uk" target="_blank"
          >How To Portage a Canoe (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/hp60rDcov48" target="_blank"
          >How To Portage for Beginners—Footwear, Gear, Tips and Techniques
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16174 mb-requirement-id-16179">
        (e) The whitewater buddy system using at least three persons and three
        craft <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BOS2DnTFRSA" target="_blank"
          >Learning How To Safely Paddle as a Group (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16180">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 12. </span>
      Participate in one or more whitewater trips using either a canoe or kayak
      on a Class I and/or Class II river. The trip(s) must involve at least six
      hours of paddling time. For each trip:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16180 mb-requirement-id-16181">
        (a) Help to prepare a written plan, specifying the route (put-ins and
        takeouts), schedule, equipment, safety precautions, and emergency
        procedures. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/HF98HTAhxuA" target="_blank"
          >Planning Your Kayak Trip Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16180 mb-requirement-id-16182">
        (b) Determine local rules and obtain permission from landowners and land
        managers in advance.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16180 mb-requirement-id-16183">
        (c) Explain what steps have been taken to comply with Scouting America
        Safety Afloat and the American Whitewater safety guidelines.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16180 mb-requirement-id-16184">
        (d) Show how to protect personal and group equipment from water and how
        to load and secure the containers in boats to be used in the trip.
        Execute the plans with other paddlers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iazzviLCqgo" target="_blank"
          >How To Pack for a Multi-Day Whitewater Trip (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/57ukrEWtvy8" target="_blank"
          >3 Minutes With a Maine Guide: Packing a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16180 mb-requirement-id-16185">
        (e) Explain to your counselor how well your plans worked for each trip
        taken.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
